# Gitconfig 

Gitconfig file is a global config file that can set some common parameters. I have listed some below, but here is a [link](https://stackoverflow.com/a/28156806) to some additional ones

```
[user]
    name = Name
    email = youremail@domain.com

[core]
    autocrlf = input # input for unix-based and true for windows ([detailed source](https://adaptivepatchwork.com/2012/03/01/mind-the-end-of-your-line/#the-old-system),[source](http://vcloud-lab.com/entries/devops/resolved-git-warning-lf-will-be-replaced-by-crlf-in-file))

[alias]
    co = checkout
    ci = commit


